        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I agree, and there are instances where GUI devs have pushed neovim core in a more GUI friendly direction. My suggestion regarding standards was intended to mean more like \"there are many ways GUIs do it, we should pick one and say 'please follow this for highlights', and possibly slowly establish that as a convention for GUIs to use for guifont as well\". Without a standard, it becomes impossible for plugin or theme developers to be consistent in how they specify fonts in a highlight group.",
